HEADWORD: fossa
<hw>fos"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>foss⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a ditch. See
<er>Fosse</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A pit, groove, cavity, or
depression, of greater or less depth; <as>as, the temporal
<ex>fossa</ex> on the side of the skull; the nasal <ex>foss⟦ae⟧</ex>
containing the nostrils in most birds.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

